    <h2>What cookies are</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small files the site saves in your browser. They remember your preferences and collect anonymized usage statistics. Without your consent, analytics cookies are not activated.</p>

    <h2>Which cookies we use</h2>
    <table class="cookies-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Cookie / record</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Lifetime</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>preferredLanguage</code> (localStorage)</td>
          <td>Stores the chosen interface language.</td>
          <td>Essential</td>
          <td>Until browser data is cleared</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>cookie_consent</code> (localStorage)</td>
          <td>Stores your cookie choice.</td>
          <td>Essential</td>
          <td>12 months</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code></td>
          <td>Google Analytics: anonymized site usage statistics.</td>
          <td>Analytics (with consent)</td>
          <td>Up to 14 months</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>How to manage</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the on-site banner — "Accept all" / "Essential only".</li>
      <li>To change your decision, clear the site cookies in your browser — the banner returns.</li>
      <li>You can disable cookies altogether in your browser settings; some site features may behave differently.</li>
    </ul>

